		<title>12KIND GALLOWS</title>
		<content>{KIND GALLOWS}                         
                                       
 Anumber of relics of Crieff's         
 turbulent past are still in existance.
 In the Town Hall may be seen the      
 timbers of the old {'kind gallows'}on 
 which those condemned at the Steward's
 Court paid the price for their crimes.
  Near the entrance to the Town Hall,  
 within an iron railing, stands the    
 ancient{stocks} that served thier     
 purpose until their use was           
 discontinued as recently as 1816.     
   Here also stands  the {mercat cross}
 of the ancient Butgh of Regality of   
 Drummond.                             
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
